#----- Snatch [General]

base feat Snatch =

  type              General;
  benefit
  "The creature can choose to start a grapple when it hits with a claw or bite
  attack, as though it had the improved grab special attack. If the creature
  gets a hold on a creature three or more sizes smaller, it squeezes each round
  for automatic bite or claw damage. A snatched opponent held in the creature’s
  mouth is not allowed a Reflex save against the creature’s breath weapon, if
  it has one.  The creature can drop a creature it has snatched as a free
  action or use a standard action to fling it aside. A flung creature travels
  1d6×10 feet, and takes 1d6 points of damage per 10 feet traveled. If the
  creature flings a snatched opponent while flying, the opponent takes this
  amount or falling damage, whichever is greater.";
  prerequisites
  "Size Huge or larger";
  worlds            Generic;
  references        WTC 17755: 304;
  description
  "The creature can grab opponents much smaller than itself and
  hold them in its mouth or claw.";
  short description "Start improved grapple when hitting with claw or bite (if three or more sizes smaller automatic bite or claw damage each round), no Ref save against breath weapon if held in mouth, can drop creature as a free action (flung 1d6 x 10 ft for 1d6 damage per 10 ft, or drop from height).".

